        public void launchApp()

        If the app fails to launch due to strange package name issues, the AccessibilityService is disabled and, to avoid busywaits, the Thread will sleep for 60 seconds.

      • writeStatusFile

        private void writeStatusFile(int status)

        Writes the .done or .failed file to notify the wrapper script to kill our process.

        The file will be created at Environment.getExternalStorageDirectory()/AppFuzzer/.

        If this fails somehow, an error message is printed and the thread sleeps for a long time.

        Parameters:
        status - int: Whether to write the done or failed file.
        0 = done, otherwise failed.

      • writeRAM

      • onAccessibilityEvent

        public void onAccessibilityEvent(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityEvent event)

        Called by the system when an event occurs.

        Locks, and then starts MyTimerTask.injectEventCaller(AccessibilityNodeInfo).

        Specified by:
        onAccessibilityEvent in class android.accessibilityservice.AccessibilityService
        Parameters:
        event - The event supplied by the Android system.

      • preprocessNode

        public void preprocessNode(android.view.accessibility.AccessibilityNodeInfo node)

        Does some preprocessing on the supplied node. Dumps the node into the private app directory (i.e. /data/data/com.example.link.appfuzzer/files/) for debugging purposes.

        Also is responsible for handling the current sets and reps. If max_sets (specified in Configuration.getMax_sets() is reached, writeStatusFile(int) is called and the Thread will wait to be killed by the wrapper script.

        Parameters:
        node - The node.
